1
00:00:26,821 --> 00:00:31,242
Raphael, stop running, you'll fall.
We're a long way from the car!

2
00:00:35,038 --> 00:00:36,247
Pretty, isn't it?

3
00:00:36,497 --> 00:00:38,416
It all seems so complicated.

4
00:00:38,666 --> 00:00:40,710
You'll see.
This will change our lives.

5
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:41,836
If you say so.

6
00:02:35,491 --> 00:02:37,201
We'll be happy in Cassis.

7
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:40,371
- We're not in Salon-de-Provence?
- Sure.

8
00:02:40,955 --> 00:02:43,207
But we'll have the seashore!

9
00:02:44,917 --> 00:02:47,545
- Don't, it's dangerous.
- I have an earplug.

10
00:02:47,795 --> 00:02:49,088
Here I am. Hello?

11
00:02:50,506 --> 00:02:54,427
Jean! Funny you should call.
We're just leaviing Cassis.

12
00:02:54,761 --> 00:02:55,845
Not good news

13
00:02:56,137 --> 00:02:57,597
about the transfer...

14
00:02:57,847 --> 00:02:59,265
I'll call you back.

15
00:02:59,807 --> 00:03:01,100
What's going on?

16
00:03:01,809 --> 00:03:03,811
- No need to quit your job.
- What?

17
00:03:04,228 --> 00:03:06,189
My transfer was denied.

18
00:03:08,066 --> 00:03:09,817
No need to get upset.

19
00:03:10,068 --> 00:03:12,570
I'm not upset. Do I seem upset?

20
00:03:13,363 --> 00:03:15,823
Then stop saying that. Shit!

21
00:03:19,494 --> 00:03:20,328
Everything OK?.

22
00:03:22,997 --> 00:03:25,875
I understand.
Just see what you can do.

23
00:03:26,125 --> 00:03:27,418
Thanks again, Jean.

24
00:03:29,962 --> 00:03:33,216
Why do you thank him?
The strings he pulled didn't help.

25
00:03:33,508 --> 00:03:37,887
Not his fault. The handicapped
come before string-pullers.

26
00:03:38,179 --> 00:03:40,348
The Riviiera is handicapped only?.

27
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,849
Of course not.

28
00:03:42,767 --> 00:03:44,394
I was so happy to move.

29
00:03:44,644 --> 00:03:45,853
You were tired of the idea.

30
00:03:46,145 --> 00:03:48,272
Because I knew we were moviing.

31
00:03:48,523 --> 00:03:51,067
Now that I know we're not,
I feel we missed out.

32
00:03:51,359 --> 00:03:53,820
- This summer...
- No! The hell with vacation!

33
00:03:54,112 --> 00:03:57,991
You said we'd move to the shore.
You worked so hard I never saw you.

34
00:03:58,282 --> 00:04:00,368
I want to live there,
Philippe Abrams!

35
00:04:00,660 --> 00:04:01,911
Yes, darling.

36
00:04:02,328 --> 00:04:03,788
- Are you upset?
- Yes, so?

37
00:04:04,122 --> 00:04:05,790
Don't be. It won't help.

38
00:04:07,375 --> 00:04:09,669
Why are you always against me?

39
00:04:33,985 --> 00:04:35,778
You're crazy to come here!

40
00:04:38,281 --> 00:04:39,824
Anybody follow you?

41
00:04:40,783 --> 00:04:42,410
Were you seen entering?

42
00:04:44,412 --> 00:04:45,496
You didn't talk to anyone?

43
00:04:45,747 --> 00:04:47,665
Come on,
we work for the post office.

44
00:04:47,915 --> 00:04:49,083
Quiet, my neck is on the line!

45
00:04:49,334 --> 00:04:51,377
No it's not. I didn't get the job.

46
00:04:51,627 --> 00:04:54,297
I'm an executive,
1 1 years busting my ass in Salon!

47
00:04:54,756 --> 00:04:56,924
If you shout, I'm done for.

48
00:04:57,216 --> 00:04:59,636
I earned that transfer,
handicapped or not.

49
00:05:00,470 --> 00:05:01,471
I'll reimburse you.

50
00:05:01,929 --> 00:05:03,973
Find me a spot.
Julie's giviing me hell.

51
00:05:07,518 --> 00:05:11,939
In Sanary-On-The-Sea,
the director's retiring in a few weeks.

52
00:05:12,607 --> 00:05:14,359
Perfect. I must have it.

53
00:05:14,692 --> 00:05:16,861
Keep your damn voice down.

54
00:05:19,822 --> 00:05:21,282
- There.
- There what?

55
00:05:23,326 --> 00:05:24,202
Yes?

56
00:05:24,786 --> 00:05:25,662
No, I'm not busy.

57
00:05:25,912 --> 00:05:26,954
The boss wants you.

58
00:05:27,288 --> 00:05:28,414
Oh. Why?.

59
00:05:28,665 --> 00:05:30,958
I don't know. You're busy?

60
00:05:31,501 --> 00:05:32,585
Be right there.

61
00:05:36,089 --> 00:05:37,840
Don't leave with me.

62
00:05:38,341 --> 00:05:40,051
Say I'm handicapped on the request.

63
00:05:40,677 --> 00:05:41,386
Are you insane?

64
00:05:41,678 --> 00:05:44,347
Why not? A mistake on a form.
What's the risk?.

65
00:05:44,597 --> 00:05:46,557
Big! Big risk!

66
00:05:46,975 --> 00:05:50,853
If they find out, you're in trouble.
But I'm dead.

67
00:05:58,486 --> 00:05:59,278
One moment.

68
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,950
Thank you for coming, Doctor.

69
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,035
- Doctor?.
- No, I'm not taking sick leave.

70
00:06:06,327 --> 00:06:07,704
It's very minor.

71
00:06:08,121 --> 00:06:09,455
Goodbye, Doctor.

72
00:06:38,568 --> 00:06:39,527
Julie!

73
00:06:49,412 --> 00:06:50,371
To Sanary!

74
00:06:50,621 --> 00:06:53,333
Thanks. You still have me for 2 days.

75
00:06:53,624 --> 00:06:56,002
Excuse me, sir.
An inspector wants to see you.

76
00:06:56,711 --> 00:06:57,545
What inspector?.

77
00:06:57,837 --> 00:06:59,589
It's about your transfer.

78
00:06:59,881 --> 00:07:01,049
- Where is he?
- In the lobby.

79
00:07:01,299 --> 00:07:03,134
Stall him for five minutes!

80
00:07:11,225 --> 00:07:12,101
Shit.

81
00:07:28,910 --> 00:07:30,620
I should have tried it out!

82
00:07:45,718 --> 00:07:47,053
I'm Philippe Abrams.

83
00:07:47,345 --> 00:07:51,432
Name's Lebic. Just a few questions
about your transfer request.

84
00:07:51,724 --> 00:07:52,850
Of course.

85
00:07:58,564 --> 00:07:59,941
Those brats.

86
00:08:00,316 --> 00:08:04,237
School kids slashed my tires.
I won't miss them.

87
00:08:04,696 --> 00:08:06,906
- Need help?
- I must do it myself.

88
00:08:08,324 --> 00:08:11,119
Sit down. I already am.

89
00:08:13,496 --> 00:08:14,664
What can I do for you?

90
00:08:14,956 --> 00:08:18,126
How long have you been
handicapped, Mr. Abrams?

91
00:08:19,502 --> 00:08:21,921
It's hard for me to remember.

92
00:08:22,797 --> 00:08:25,091
I was little. It's all a blur.

93
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:28,469
Reliviing it is traumatic.

94
00:08:31,848 --> 00:08:32,724
Sorry.

95
00:08:33,016 --> 00:08:34,892
Muscle spasms.

96
00:08:39,230 --> 00:08:40,690
It's over. I'm fine.

97
00:08:45,028 --> 00:08:48,072
Mr. Abrams. I have
two transfer requests in your name.

98
00:08:48,448 --> 00:08:51,576
One, recently,
for a limited-mobility person,

99
00:08:51,826 --> 00:08:52,910
for the Sanary spot.

100
00:08:53,161 --> 00:08:56,289
The other, for Cassis,
6 months ago. No handicap.

101
00:08:56,581 --> 00:08:59,250
Did you make both requests?

102
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:06,632
I made both requests.

103
00:09:07,091 --> 00:09:08,426
Yes.

104
00:09:09,385 --> 00:09:10,678
The first,

105
00:09:10,887 --> 00:09:12,639
as non-handicapped,

106
00:09:12,972 --> 00:09:15,558
because I wanted to be
treated as normal.

107
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,310
Like anyone else.

108
00:09:17,894 --> 00:09:18,936
It's important to us,

109
00:09:19,187 --> 00:09:20,647
the handicapped,

110
00:09:21,731 --> 00:09:26,235
to be seen by people like you
as deserviing more than pity.

111
00:09:27,445 --> 00:09:29,197
That's very laudable.

112
00:09:30,156 --> 00:09:33,034
Of course,
if my transfer depends on it...

113
00:09:33,326 --> 00:09:34,369
No, not at all.

114
00:09:34,619 --> 00:09:37,538
This is just
an obligatory verification.

115
00:09:38,539 --> 00:09:41,250
You know, I often
get false declarations

116
00:09:41,501 --> 00:09:44,337
in requests for sought-after posts,
like the Riviiera.

117
00:09:44,671 --> 00:09:46,255
- No!
- It's rampant.

118
00:09:47,632 --> 00:09:48,633
How shameful!

119
00:09:48,925 --> 00:09:50,677
You can say that again.

120
00:09:51,886 --> 00:09:53,846
You'll love Sanary.

121
00:09:55,723 --> 00:09:57,433
I won't bother you anymore.

122
00:09:57,684 --> 00:09:59,394
Not at all.
Goodbye, Mr. Lebic.

123
00:10:02,105 --> 00:10:03,564
How shameful.

124
00:10:07,777 --> 00:10:08,820
Nut job.

125
00:10:09,404 --> 00:10:10,780
You're a total nut job.

126
00:10:12,699 --> 00:10:15,410
You're my friend.
You'll fix this.

127
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:17,203
I'll fix nothing.

128
00:10:17,620 --> 00:10:20,456
Don't you dare say we're friends.
Not here.

129
00:10:20,832 --> 00:10:23,501
Not a handicap imposter.

130
00:10:24,502 --> 00:10:27,964
I only did it for Julie.
I'm terribly sorry.

131
00:10:30,591 --> 00:10:31,384
All right.

132
00:10:32,885 --> 00:10:34,053
Good news and bad news.

133
00:10:34,512 --> 00:10:35,513
I've been suspended?

134
00:10:36,681 --> 00:10:37,265
Worse.

135
00:10:37,765 --> 00:10:38,641
Fired?

136
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:39,684
Worse.

137
00:10:40,018 --> 00:10:42,395
- Worse than fired?
- Transferred up north.

138
00:10:42,645 --> 00:10:44,188
North? Not Lyons!

139
00:10:44,564 --> 00:10:47,025
No, not Lyons. The north north.

140
00:10:47,317 --> 00:10:49,235
Not Paris. Don't tell me.

141
00:10:49,902 --> 00:10:51,029
Not Paris.

142
00:10:51,738 --> 00:10:52,488
Farther north.

143
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:53,573
Belgium?

144
00:10:54,115 --> 00:10:56,159
No. Before Belgium, there's...

145
00:10:56,409 --> 00:10:58,077
The North region. Near Lille.

146
00:10:58,369 --> 00:10:59,662
Little what?

147
00:10:59,954 --> 00:11:01,831
No! The city of Lille.

148
00:11:02,123 --> 00:11:03,249
Lille? That's horrible.

149
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,251
Starts next Monday.

150
00:11:05,710 --> 00:11:06,753
This coming Monday?.

151
00:11:07,003 --> 00:11:10,923
I can't. I have no warm clothes.
No place to live.

152
00:11:11,507 --> 00:11:14,510
There's an apartment
for the local manager.

153
00:11:15,386 --> 00:11:16,804
What's the place?

154
00:11:17,472 --> 00:11:18,222
Bergues.

155
00:11:21,476 --> 00:11:22,435
I'll refuse it.

156
00:11:22,727 --> 00:11:24,103
Can't. It's disciplinary.

157
00:11:26,272 --> 00:11:27,315
What's the good news?

158
00:11:28,399 --> 00:11:29,067
That was it.

159
00:11:30,526 --> 00:11:31,736
What's the bad news?

160
00:11:31,986 --> 00:11:32,945
You stay there 2 years.

161
00:11:35,531 --> 00:11:37,492
- Two years?
- Minimum.

162
00:11:37,784 --> 00:11:39,327
Two years in the north. No!

163
00:11:40,119 --> 00:11:42,622
It's the north or you're fired. Sorry.

164
00:11:42,914 --> 00:11:45,458
How can I tell Julie?
She thinks it's Sanary.

165
00:11:46,959 --> 00:11:49,253
You leave when the coast is clear.

166
00:11:56,344 --> 00:11:57,345
Now!

167
00:12:04,811 --> 00:12:06,062
Hi, honey.

168
00:12:09,816 --> 00:12:12,527
I'm looking at apartments
in Sanary. Great.

169
00:12:12,944 --> 00:12:14,070
We must hurry.

170
00:12:14,362 --> 00:12:15,446
Don't worry, it's off.

171
00:12:15,905 --> 00:12:16,906
It fell through.

172
00:12:17,198 --> 00:12:18,616
Another handicapped guy?.

173
00:12:19,450 --> 00:12:20,493
Sort of.

174
00:12:20,743 --> 00:12:22,495
- I can't believe it.
- Hang on.

175
00:12:22,787 --> 00:12:24,706
They offered better.

176
00:12:25,748 --> 00:12:27,583
You scared me. Where?

177
00:12:29,335 --> 00:12:30,753
- Bergues.
- Where?

178
00:12:31,713 --> 00:12:32,797
Beautiful Bergues.

179
00:12:34,966 --> 00:12:36,801
In the north.
Isn't that wonderful?

180
00:12:37,844 --> 00:12:38,845
What did you do?

181
00:12:39,137 --> 00:12:40,096
Me? Nothing.

182
00:12:40,388 --> 00:12:41,556
I'm not an idiot.

183
00:12:41,973 --> 00:12:45,226
If you do well, you stay south.
You must've screwed up big-time.

184
00:12:45,810 --> 00:12:47,603
No, it's just the opposite.

185
00:12:47,854 --> 00:12:50,398
They offered me 2 years up north.
I earn points,

186
00:12:50,648 --> 00:12:53,067
get priority
for all the Riviiera jobs.

187
00:12:53,318 --> 00:12:56,446
In terms of index,
after 2 years in the north,

188
00:12:56,696 --> 00:12:58,156
it's like I'm handicapped!

189
00:12:58,448 --> 00:13:00,533
Turn it down. I won't freeze.

190
00:13:00,992 --> 00:13:03,953
Who's going to freeze?
We're not liviing outdoors up there.

191
00:13:04,203 --> 00:13:04,912
Dad,

192
00:13:05,204 --> 00:13:06,247
I'll lose my toes.

193
00:13:06,539 --> 00:13:07,582
Why would you?

194
00:13:07,874 --> 00:13:08,958
Not the North Pole.

195
00:13:09,584 --> 00:13:11,627
Not the North Pole. The north!

196
00:13:11,919 --> 00:13:13,755
The truth. What did you do?

197
00:13:14,047 --> 00:13:16,549
I got a great promotion.
I don't get this.

198
00:13:17,634 --> 00:13:18,635
I'll call Jean.

199
00:13:22,347 --> 00:13:24,891
To get the Sanary job,
I said I was handicapped.

200
00:13:25,183 --> 00:13:26,809
You pretended you were handicapped?

201
00:13:27,101 --> 00:13:27,977
I'm sorry.

202
00:13:28,269 --> 00:13:30,104
Go to the North Pole alone!

203
00:14:06,933 --> 00:14:07,725
What is it?

204
00:14:10,144 --> 00:14:12,689
Recognize me?
I married Julie, your niece.

205
00:14:14,065 --> 00:14:18,027
Right, she said you'd come bug me.
What do you want?

206
00:14:22,490 --> 00:14:25,159
I have to go to the North region.

207
00:14:25,368 --> 00:14:26,327
A transfer.

208
00:14:26,577 --> 00:14:28,705
Julie said you know
the area near Lille.

209
00:14:29,998 --> 00:14:34,377
In 1934, my mother
slept with a Sheutemi.

210
00:14:35,003 --> 00:14:35,920
What?

211
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:38,256
I said, in 1934,

212
00:14:38,673 --> 00:14:41,342
my mother slept with a Sheutemi.

213
00:14:41,718 --> 00:14:42,468
A shut-in?

214
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,470
Not a shut-in!

215
00:14:44,721 --> 00:14:46,014
A Sheutemi.

216
00:14:46,264 --> 00:14:51,060
That's what they call people up there.
Men, women, children! Sheutemi!

217
00:14:51,644 --> 00:14:52,645
Shutemies?

218
00:14:52,937 --> 00:14:56,316
Even animals are Sheutemi! Dogs...

219
00:14:56,774 --> 00:14:59,652
Cats are sheutemi.

220
00:15:00,194 --> 00:15:03,156
Cows, chickens, calves
are all sheutemi.

221
00:15:03,614 --> 00:15:04,949
And the language is sheutemi, too.

222
00:15:05,450 --> 00:15:07,618
They say O instead of A,

223
00:15:08,161 --> 00:15:10,997
SHKA instead of SH,
and they say SH...

224
00:15:11,331 --> 00:15:13,708
but instead of S.
They're crackpots!

225
00:15:15,710 --> 00:15:17,128
Just when you think you got it,

226
00:15:17,378 --> 00:15:21,174
they tell you a "mop"
is a wassingue!

227
00:15:24,844 --> 00:15:27,055
And what's life like there?

228
00:15:27,430 --> 00:15:28,389
Pretty easy?.

229
00:15:28,681 --> 00:15:31,225
Rough! Very rough!

230
00:15:31,851 --> 00:15:34,520
Only the ones in coal
live well.

231
00:15:35,563 --> 00:15:37,273
The others are just...

232
00:15:37,732 --> 00:15:39,525
miserable.

233
00:15:39,859 --> 00:15:42,445
They die very young there.

234
00:15:42,695 --> 00:15:45,365
Good thing my mother
came back south.

235
00:15:45,782 --> 00:15:49,243
I was ten.
I couldn't stand the cold.

236
00:15:49,911 --> 00:15:51,204
It's cold up there?

237
00:15:53,289 --> 00:15:55,833
Summer's all right.
About thirty degrees.

238
00:15:56,125 --> 00:15:59,128
But in winter it goes
down, down, down.

239
00:15:59,379 --> 00:16:02,507
Twenty, zero, minus twenty!
Minus fifty!

240
00:16:03,132 --> 00:16:06,219
You figure you'll stay in bed.
It goes to minus 60!

241
00:16:06,594 --> 00:16:07,553
Minus 60?

242
00:16:07,887 --> 00:16:09,555
The north!

243
00:16:11,057 --> 00:16:12,684
You asked, kid.

244
00:16:13,226 --> 00:16:14,978
It's the north.

245
00:16:16,354 --> 00:16:17,522
Got your answer?.

246
00:16:18,856 --> 00:16:20,066
Good.

247
00:16:51,180 --> 00:16:52,140
See? Freezing fog.

248
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:54,767
- What's freezing fog?
- A horror.

249
00:16:55,727 --> 00:16:59,397
Look. 40 in the morning,
fifty at midday. Not that cold!

250
00:16:59,981 --> 00:17:01,441
Think those are real?

251
00:17:02,817 --> 00:17:03,526
Aren't they?.

252
00:17:03,776 --> 00:17:08,156
Open your eyes. Regional officials
pressure the weather serviice.

253
00:17:08,406 --> 00:17:10,825
- Or no one would go there.
- Think so?

254
00:17:12,452 --> 00:17:13,911
Freezing fog.

255
00:17:16,956 --> 00:17:18,082
Bergues.

256
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:19,834
Probably not in there.

257
00:17:20,084 --> 00:17:21,794
Calculating route.

258
00:17:22,045 --> 00:17:22,795
It is.

259
00:17:23,838 --> 00:17:25,131
Shut up, bitch.

260
00:17:37,602 --> 00:17:39,604
I can't go.
I'm not strong enough.

261
00:17:40,063 --> 00:17:42,357
You're better off here,
with the boy.

262
00:17:43,483 --> 00:17:44,734
Don't take that off.

263
00:17:44,984 --> 00:17:47,278
I'll be too hot on the way up.

264
00:17:47,528 --> 00:17:49,947
Better you get used to wearing it.

265
00:17:58,039 --> 00:17:59,082
Raphael,

266
00:17:59,707 --> 00:18:00,750
take care of Mom.

267
00:18:01,042 --> 00:18:02,085
- I'm counting on you.
- OK, Dad.

