between humans.

952
01:01:18,640 --> 01:01:20,350
However, with objects...

953
01:01:23,186 --> 01:01:24,437
You're sick!

954
01:01:26,230 --> 01:01:27,190
Stop!

955
01:01:30,234 --> 01:01:32,528
Stop that.
Come on, give me a hand!

956
01:01:33,112 --> 01:01:33,863
Stop it.

957
01:01:40,495 --> 01:01:41,496
Mr. Abrams...

958
01:01:42,914 --> 01:01:44,457
- He's not well.
- He's fine.

959
01:01:44,707 --> 01:01:46,209
- He's not answering.
- He's fine.

960
01:01:46,459 --> 01:01:48,086
Come on, boss.

961
01:01:52,590 --> 01:01:54,008
He can't shay no.

962
01:01:54,300 --> 01:01:55,677
You know how it is.

963
01:01:55,927 --> 01:01:59,514
You go see people,
bring the mail,

964
01:01:59,764 --> 01:02:02,225
so it's "Have a little drink."

965
01:02:02,725 --> 01:02:03,685
Little by little...

966
01:02:03,977 --> 01:02:06,896
He winds up fighting outside,
in uniform. That's intolerable.

967
01:02:07,146 --> 01:02:08,606
He can't say no. I say stop!

968
01:02:08,898 --> 01:02:11,025
An official reprimand is a lot.

969
01:02:11,317 --> 01:02:12,735
Are you defending him?

970
01:02:13,027 --> 01:02:14,779
I'm not defending him.

971
01:02:15,738 --> 01:02:16,906
I want him to get better.

972
01:02:17,156 --> 01:02:19,367
Reprimanding him won't help.

973
01:02:19,659 --> 01:02:22,120
You know what Antoine's problem is?

974
01:02:22,453 --> 01:02:23,746
He's in love with you.

975
01:02:26,666 --> 01:02:27,959
Well actually...

976
01:02:28,501 --> 01:02:30,003
we were together for a year.

977
01:02:30,294 --> 01:02:31,170
Why'd you leave?

978
01:02:32,213 --> 01:02:33,214
He left me.

979
01:02:34,257 --> 01:02:35,258
I don't understand.

980
01:02:35,550 --> 01:02:37,510
I was very much in love.

981
01:02:37,760 --> 01:02:40,596
I stood up to his mother,
who's very overbearing.

982
01:02:41,514 --> 01:02:42,765
I got very mad.

983
01:02:43,558 --> 01:02:46,436
And I told Antoine to choose.
He chose her.

984
01:02:46,728 --> 01:02:49,897
So? I'm a postal manager,
not a social worker.

985
01:03:45,078 --> 01:03:47,288
Beautiful, Antoine. Keep playing.

986
01:03:54,545 --> 01:03:58,132
Are you here to give me
a music degree or a reprimand?

987
01:03:58,424 --> 01:04:00,426
Why don't you talk
to your mother?.

988
01:04:01,552 --> 01:04:05,139
I spoke to Annabelle.
Your mom's the source of the problem.

989
01:04:11,729 --> 01:04:15,024
I have to be kind to my mom.
She's had a hard life.

990
01:04:15,400 --> 01:04:17,986
By not telling her
what's on your mind?

991
01:04:20,154 --> 01:04:21,656
We're all the same.

992
01:04:21,948 --> 01:04:24,784
I love my wife,
but I lie to her all weekend.

993
01:04:25,034 --> 01:04:25,660
Why?.

994
01:04:25,910 --> 01:04:27,203
It's a long story.

995
01:04:27,996 --> 01:04:30,665
- I didn't know you were married.
- I am.

996
01:04:30,915 --> 01:04:34,043
Then why doesn't she come
and live here with you?

997
01:04:35,753 --> 01:04:37,255
My wife is...

998
01:04:38,798 --> 01:04:41,843
Depressed. Clinically, even.

999
01:04:43,303 --> 01:04:45,346
If she came north, she'd get worse.

1000
01:04:45,763 --> 01:04:46,514
Why?.

1001
01:04:46,806 --> 01:04:50,268
I mean, it would be worse
for her to leave home.

1002
01:04:50,560 --> 01:04:51,436
Wherever she went.

1003
01:04:52,895 --> 01:04:53,855
I see.

1004
01:04:54,147 --> 01:04:56,316
Antoine, all I'm asking

1005
01:04:56,566 --> 01:04:58,318
is to go easy at work.

1006
01:04:58,609 --> 01:05:02,280
Drinking won't make it better.
It can only get worse.

1007
01:05:02,613 --> 01:05:04,032
I acted like a babash.

1008
01:05:05,325 --> 01:05:06,284
We all make mistakes.

1009
01:05:06,534 --> 01:05:08,703
What counts is how you fix it.

1010
01:05:10,413 --> 01:05:11,456
It can't be fixed.

1011
01:05:11,748 --> 01:05:13,333
You can fix anything.

1012
01:05:13,750 --> 01:05:15,168
Except maybe his motorcycle.

1013
01:05:17,962 --> 01:05:18,755
You want to try?.

1014
01:05:19,005 --> 01:05:20,965
- What?
- The carillon!

1015
01:05:22,717 --> 01:05:25,386
You must know a tune.
It's like a piano.

1016
01:05:26,638 --> 01:05:28,222
Everyone will hear.

1017
01:05:28,473 --> 01:05:30,350
Plug in the earphones.

1018
01:05:31,601 --> 01:05:32,894
Go ahead, biloute.

1019
01:05:34,270 --> 01:05:35,813
Not that one.

1020
01:05:37,398 --> 01:05:38,399
Not easy.

1021
01:05:38,650 --> 01:05:39,567
Higher.

1022
01:05:56,209 --> 01:05:57,543
Antoine, wait!

1023
01:05:58,378 --> 01:05:59,754
I'm coming with you.

1024
01:06:01,005 --> 01:06:02,215
I know my route.

1025
01:06:02,465 --> 01:06:05,468
I'm coming along.
You have to learn to say no.

1026
01:06:05,969 --> 01:06:07,387
You're the bosh.

1027
01:06:27,365 --> 01:06:28,241
Hey, biloute!

1028
01:06:28,533 --> 01:06:29,242
Mr. Mahieux.

1029
01:06:29,492 --> 01:06:32,161
Hi. Philippe Abrams,
the post office manager.

1030
01:06:32,453 --> 01:06:33,871
Nice of you to come.

1031
01:06:34,122 --> 01:06:35,248
Come in a minute.

1032
01:06:35,999 --> 01:06:39,252
No, thank you Mr. Mahieux.
We'll be moviing on.

1033
01:06:39,502 --> 01:06:40,878
Too early for cocktails.

1034
01:06:41,754 --> 01:06:45,091
- How about coffee?
- That's different. Fine.

1035
01:06:46,301 --> 01:06:48,761
- A little juniper?.
- Not for me.

1036
01:06:49,429 --> 01:06:50,138
No, thank you.

1037
01:06:50,388 --> 01:06:53,266
It'll warm you up.
A southerner like yourshelf!

1038
01:06:57,520 --> 01:06:58,730
